Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Or use the cross-platform approach** — override `CreateWindow` in `App.cs` and subscribe to the `Stopped` event, which maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* runs on both platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```

**Key notes:**
- `Deactivated` maps to Android `OnPause` (focus lost but may still be visible)
- `Stopped` maps to Android `OnStop` / iOS `DidEnterBackground` (fully backgrounded)
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS
- On Android, the back button can skip `Stopped` — also save in `Destroying`
